task.summary: Default task
Started application: Built main launcher activity. Added logo to application.
Started application: Built and designed main launcher activity, created log in and main feed activities.
Added Parse SDK to app lib and gradle dependencies. Created conneciton check and check if user is connected to parse or not.
Log in view created, button listeners are working, email and password fields gather information.
Finished log/in register buttons, registering opens up registration activity. Registration activity design started.
Registration Activity validates edit text fields.
Registration Activity registers new user and transfers to launch activity when successful or toasts user when unsuccessful.

Registering saves user name and moves to launch activity. Launch activity is complete, as it now transitions to the main feed when users are logged in. Added action bar on main feed. Action bar log out logs user out and returns to launch.

Log in activity verifies fields are not empty and toasts if necesssary, Log in button logs user in if fields are accurate, toasts if not. Milestone 1 complete for Log in Activity, Launch Activity, and Registration Activity.

Add Post story layout created, text and media fragments created and display when user opens post story activity from main feed. Fixed EditText view background, changed action bar to blue. Need to fix text color.
Post Stroy activity implements share listener on action bar to get values from the text fragment.

Share post activity presents user with dialog requiring confirmation prior to sharing a post. Permission to share value is saved to shared preference and user data on Parse. Shared preference is updated each time user loggs in on Log In Activity, and a default is set when registering new user. Edit Text views get data and pass them to Activity when user shares a story, but doesn't share yet.

Media Button launch intents for both the camera and the gallery. This completes Milestone 1. For Milestone 2, both intents return an image if one was selected. The cancel fragment replaces the media button fragment, and the image is displayed within the image view.
Added Facebook SDK, user can log in through Facebook, fixed login and register textviews so the line is not missing on activity load.

Added custom alert with edit text field to gather an entered email address to reset the user's password for log in. Email is verified prior to checking, and a toast alerts the user if any errors occur.
Register activity now returns image from camera, makes a thumbnail image, converts that to a circular image, sets within frame, and displays in imageview.
Registration activity checks for image when user registers. If image is found, saves the image, and registers the new user with their image as a png.

Created subclass for story post and user. Story posts successfully save stories with or without image and upon success return the user to the main feed. If there is an error, user is alerted. Cancel fragment now removes image and returns media fragment upon selection. Moved some camera functions to HelperMethods class.

Fixed StoryAuthor subclass from ParseObject to ParseUser, Began custom adapter that shows post title and converted time stamp on user stories, Built custom query for stories that include the author's name, and returns them with the newest ones first, Created listview and started list item. Returned query displays items within listview. Fized StoryPost subclass to return StoryAuthor instead of ParseUser.

User profile image views not displaying correctly on emulator, changed to CircleImageView. Removed code and drawables from previous circle frame. Added progress dialogs when user registers or shares a post.
Changed ParseUser to StoryAuthor to match subclass registered in Launch Activity. Main Feed updates upon new post share. Removed custom image name as some were causing save errors.

Started tasks for release candidate. Added methods in StoryAuthor subclass to retrieve user's id, and the object ID in the StoryPost subclass. In the Custom story adapter, created functions to retrieve the remaining values for the Main Feed posts. An interface is defined in the Main Feed that returns the list item's specified id when the user selects one of the buttons within the adapter's listview items. Also, the activity, fragments, and layouts for the User Details activity were began.

Added dialog fragment for list dialog when user flags a post. Created subclass for flags and registered it in the launch activity. Added icons for flag, add, and share actions. Created methods to share and flag posts when user clicks listview item buttons.

Fixed main feed custom adapter to display the users profile picture instead of the story picture. Added methods on main feed to flag a story, or open the user details when their name is selected. User Details activity retrieves the id, then queries for that user's stories. The returned list is passed to the user list fragment, and the user to the user profile fragment which displays the user's name and image. User Detail Activity layout, and User Profile Fragment layouts are started.

User Display view edit fragment is displayed when user selects the edit button on action bar, upon close/cancel the main fragment is returned and name and image saves and updates on save. This fragment is also only visible to the current user. Also updated the OnShareListener to another package with the OnEdit one.

Changed user stories fragment to a List Fragment, and upon creation set the custom adapter to the list adapter. Changed CustomUserStoriesAdapter from ParseQuery adapter to Base Adapter. Updated Layouts for User Details activity, stories fragment, and items.

Parse and Facebook Imageviews were switched for a Picasso one, the images now stop disappearing and load more smoothly. Also added a default image in case the user doesn't have one, and changed the compression when uploading images to account for images that were too big for Parse (within a try/catch block). Also changed story image views, and removed the image if there is not one. Fixed Facebook to remove session access when user logs out of the application so when logging in it will retrieve the current logged in facebook account rather than the former one. Fixed user detail stories to display most recent stories first. User profile picture within main list now launches detail view. Up navigation works on both Share Post and User Details activities. Added remaining application files to Git.
Added informational comments within each java class. Final commit for Good Feed's release candidate.
